ide.backend.model

Class BlockModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • ide.backend.model.BlockModel
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractRefVariabelModel, AbstractVariableModel, AccessModel, ChangeAppearanceModel, CharAtModel, ClassModel, ConcatModel, ConnectedBlocks, EmitModel, EventModel, ForeverModel, FunctionCallModel, HideModel, IfBlockModel, IfElseModel, InstanceModel, LengthModel, LockModel, MoveModel, OperatorModel, PrintModel, RandomModel, RefEventModel, ReturnModel, SetModel, ShowModel, SleepModel, TopLevelModel, TypeModel, UnLockModel, UnOperatorModel, ValueModel, WhileModel, WireFrameModel, WireModel

    public abstract class BlockModel
extends java.util.Observable
    This abstract Class is the base class for all usable blockmodels in the IDE. It contains all common properties. The position of block in the IDE. DEFAULT: (0,0) If the code of the block is run boolean [_debug] DEFAULT: false.
    Author:
    matthijs

      • tellParentChanged

        public abstract void tellParentChanged(BlockModel child,
                                       Variable.VariableType type)
        If the parent of a block that its changed so that typechecking or other error detection can be preformed. This is an upwards chain in the tree if models. If this function is not relevant the block can stop the chain by not calling his parent.
        Parameters:
        child - child calling this function
        type - type of variable of the child.
